Implement the client-side SignalR integration in `Homespun.Client` to support real-time updates from the server. This is critical for the Claude Code session UI which relies heavily on real-time streaming.

## Current architecture (Blazor Server)
In the current Blazor Server app, components are server-side and live in the same process as the SignalR hubs. The `ClaudeCodeHub` broadcasts messages via `IHubContext<ClaudeCodeHub>` and components receive updates via injected services and `InvokeAsync(StateHasChanged)`.

## New architecture (Blazor WASM)
In WASM, the client runs in the browser and needs to connect to SignalR hubs over WebSocket. The client must:
1. Establish a `HubConnection` to the server
2. Register handlers for server-to-client messages
3. Invoke hub methods for client-to-server communication
4. Manage connection lifecycle (connect, reconnect, disconnect)

## Services to create

### ClaudeCodeSignalRService
```csharp
// Homespun.Client/Services/ClaudeCodeSignalRService.cs
public class ClaudeCodeSignalRService : IAsyncDisposable
{
    private HubConnection? _hubConnection;

    // Connection management
    Task ConnectAsync();
    Task DisconnectAsync();
    bool IsConnected { get; }

    // Client-to-server methods (matching ClaudeCodeHub methods)
    Task JoinSessionAsync(string sessionId);
    Task LeaveSessionAsync(string sessionId);
    Task SendMessageAsync(string sessionId, string message, string? permissionMode = null);
    Task StopSessionAsync(string sessionId);
    Task InterruptSessionAsync(string sessionId);
    Task<IReadOnlyList<ClaudeSession>> GetAllSessionsAsync();
    Task<IReadOnlyList<ClaudeSession>> GetProjectSessionsAsync(string projectId);
    Task<ClaudeSession?> GetSessionAsync(string sessionId);
    Task AnswerQuestionAsync(string sessionId, string answersJson);
    Task ExecutePlanAsync(string sessionId, bool clearContext = false);

    // Events for server-to-client messages
    event Action<ClaudeSession>? OnSessionStarted;
    event Action<string>? OnSessionStopped;
    event Action<string, ClaudeMessage>? OnMessageReceived;
    event Action<string, ClaudeMessageContent>? OnContentBlockReceived;
    event Action<string, ClaudeSessionStatus>? OnSessionStatusChanged;
    event Action<string, decimal, long>? OnSessionResultReceived;
    event Action<string, ClaudeMessageContent, int?>? OnStreamingContentStarted;
    event Action<string, ClaudeMessageContent, string, int?>? OnStreamingContentDelta;
    event Action<string, ClaudeMessageContent, int?>? OnStreamingContentStopped;
    event Action<string, PendingQuestion>? OnQuestionReceived;
    event Action<string>? OnQuestionAnswered;
    event Action<string>? OnContextCleared;
}
```

### NotificationSignalRService
```csharp
// Homespun.Client/Services/NotificationSignalRService.cs
public class NotificationSignalRService : IAsyncDisposable
{
    private HubConnection? _hubConnection;

    Task ConnectAsync();
    Task DisconnectAsync();

    event Action<NotificationDto>? OnNotificationReceived;
    event Action<string>? OnNotificationDismissed;
}
```

## Hub connection setup
```csharp
_hubConnection = new HubConnectionBuilder()
    .WithUrl(navigationManager.ToAbsoluteUri(HubConstants.ClaudeCodeHubUrl))
    .WithAutomaticReconnect()
    .Build();

// Register all handlers
_hubConnection.On<ClaudeSession>("SessionStarted", session =>
    OnSessionStarted?.Invoke(session));

_hubConnection.On<string, ClaudeMessageContent, string, int?>("StreamingContentDelta",
    (sessionId, content, delta, index) =>
        OnStreamingContentDelta?.Invoke(sessionId, content, delta, index));

// ... register all other handlers
```

## Integration with components

### Session page pattern
```razor
@inject ClaudeCodeSignalRService SignalR

@code {
    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
    {
        await SignalR.ConnectAsync();
        SignalR.OnStreamingContentDelta += HandleStreamingDelta;
        SignalR.OnSessionStatusChanged += HandleStatusChange;
        await SignalR.JoinSessionAsync(sessionId);
    }

    private void HandleStreamingDelta(string sid, ClaudeMessageContent content, string delta, int? index)
    {
        if (sid != sessionId) return;
        InvokeAsync(() => {
            // Update UI with streaming content
            StateHasChanged();
        });
    }

    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync()
    {
        SignalR.OnStreamingContentDelta -= HandleStreamingDelta;
        await SignalR.LeaveSessionAsync(sessionId);
    }
}
```

## Reconnection handling
- Use `.WithAutomaticReconnect()` with custom retry policy
- Show a reconnection banner/overlay when disconnected (similar to current `ReconnectModal.razor` but adapted for WASM)
- Re-join session groups on reconnection

## Hub URL configuration
Use `HubConstants` from `Homespun.Shared` for hub URLs:
- `HubConstants.ClaudeCodeHubUrl` = "/hubs/claudecode"
- `HubConstants.NotificationHubUrl` = "/hubs/notifications"

Since the WASM client is served from the same origin as the server, relative URLs work without CORS issues.

## DI registration
```csharp
// Program.cs
builder.Services.AddScoped<ClaudeCodeSignalRService>();
builder.Services.AddScoped<NotificationSignalRService>();
```

## Verification
- SignalR connection established on page load
- Session streaming works end-to-end (start session → see real-time message streaming)
- Notification toasts appear when server sends notifications
- Reconnection works after brief disconnection
- No memory leaks from event handler subscriptions
